  I-INTRODUCTION.                                                 9443 1451
          The resonance parameters of the neutron cross sections  9443 1451
of 241Pu were obtained by Derrien and de Saussure(2) in the energy9443 1451
range from thermal to 300 eV by a Bayesian fit of selected        9443 1451
experimental effective total cross sections, fission and capture  9443 1451
cross sections by using the Reich-Moore fitting code SAMMY(5).    9443 1451
The results of this work were used in the ENDF/B-VI evaluated data9443 1451
file.  Some difficulties were encountered in the normalization of 9443 1451
the experimental fission cross sections due to the discrepancies  9443 1451
in the shape of the available experimental data both in thermal   9443 1451
and high energy ranges.  The consistency among the experimental   9443 1451
data base could not be obtained without large renormalization and 9443 1451
background correction parameters in the SAMMY fits.  Particularly,9443 1451
it was shown that the discrepancy between the fission cross       9443 1451
sections in the thermal energy range was due to a deviation from  9443 1451
the 1/v shape below about 0.05 eV.                                9443 1451
          New fission cross section measurements were recently    9443 1451
performed by Wagemans et al.(1,6) in the energy range from 0.002  9443 1451
eV to 20 eV in order to check the shape of the cross section in   9443 1451
the thermal energy range.  They showed that the shape of the      9443 1451
fission cross section was clearly compatible with the 1/v law,in  9443 1451
contradiction to all the previous measurements reported in the    9443 1451
literature.  Consequently, the normalization of all the           9443 1451
previous results using the low energy region could be erroneous.  9443 1451
Particularly,the discrepancy observed in the average fission      9443 1451
cross section over the 0.26 eV resonance could be due to the      9443 1451
errors of normalization in the thermal region.  Wagemans et al.   9443 1451
compared the ENDF/B-VI data to their new results and concluded    9443 1451
that the evaluated data files using the evaluation of Derrien and 9443 1451
de Saussure should be revised in the energy range up to 300 eV.   9443 1451
                                                                  9443 1451
   II-COMMENTS ON ENDF/B-VI EVALUATION.                           9443 1451
  In the energy range from 0.01 eV to 3 eV the new data of        9443 1451
Wagemans et al. are on average 2.2% smaller than ENDF/B-VI.  This 9443 1451
difference is mainly due a difference of 3% between the 1976 data 9443 1451
of Wagemans et al.(7) and the new values of Wagemans et al. The   9443 1451
1976 data of Wagemans et al. were used in the evaluation of       9443 1451
Derrien and de Saussure in the low energy region.                 9443 1451
          In the intermediate energy range from 3 eV to 12 eV,the 9443 1451
average fission of ENDF/B-VI is in excellent agreement with the   9443 1451
new data of Wagemans et al. In this energy range,the SAMMY fits of9443 1451
Derrien and de Saussure were performed on the fission cross       9443 1451
section of Weston and Todd(8),of Blons(9) and of Migneco et al.   9443 1451
(10) with an adjustment of the normalization factor and of the    9443 1451
background correction parameters of all the experimental data; the9443 1451
agreement between the new data of Wagemans et al. and ENDF/B-VI   9443 1451
shows that, at least in this energy range, SAMMY performed on the 9443 1451
data of Weston and Todd a renormalization equivalent to that      9443 1451
recommended by Wagemans et al.(1).                                9443 1451
          In the higher range up to 300 eV,the SAMMY fits relied  9443 1451
mainly on the high resolution measurements of Blons and of        9443 1451
Migneco et al. for the accurate determination of the resonance    9443 1451
parameters.  Quite large normalization coefficients and background9443 1451
correction parameters were also needed in this energy range to    9443 1451
obtain the consistency between the calculated cross sections and  9443 1451
the experimental data. However,the result of the fits was in quite9443 1451
good agreement with the data of Weston and Todd normalized to the 9443 1451
1976 data of Wagemans et al.in the low energy region, which is    9443 1451
also equivalent to the normalization to the 1983 data of Wagemans 9443 1451
et al.(11).  Since the earlier data of Wagemans et al. should     9443 1451
decrease by 3% to be consistent with the new data, it is likely   9443 1451
that the ENDF/B-VI fission cross section could be too large by    9443 1451
about 3% in the energy range above 12 eV.                         9443 1451
                                                                  9443 1451
  III-REVISION OF THE RESONANCE PARAMETERS.                       9443 1451
         An accurate up-dating of the 241Pu resonance parameters  9443 1451
could be obtained by renormalizing the fission experimental data  9443 1451
base according to the new data of Wagemans et al. and by          9443 1451
restarting the SAMMY fits of the new experimental data base,      9443 1451
including the high resolution transmission data of Harvey and     9443 1451
Simpson(12).  Due to lack of time a new SAMMY analysis was        9443 1451
performed only in the energy range from 0.002 eV to 3 eV.  In the 9443 1451
energy range above 3 eV the up-dating was performed by applying   9443 1451
some small corrections to the resonance parameters.               9443 1451
       The SAMMY analysis of the new Wagemans et al. data was     9443 1451
performed along with the total cross section of Young and         9443 1451
Smith(13) in the energy range from 0.002 eV to 3 eV,by starting   9443 1451
with the ENDF/B-VI resonance parameters.  Only the parameters of  9443 1451
the 3+ resonances at -0.122 eV and at 0.265 eV were adjusted in   9443 1451
this energy range.  The values of the cross sections calculated   9443 1451
at 0.0253 eV are compared to the standard data(14) in Table 1. The9443 1451
average total,fission and capture cross sections calculated with  9443 1451
the new resonance parameters are displayed on Table 2,3 and 4 with9443 1451
the corresponding experimental data and the values obtained from  9443 1451
ENDF/B-VI.  One should point out that an energy shift of          9443 1451
dE/E=+0.00384 was applied to the data of Young and Smith in order 9443 1451
to achieve a good consistency with the energy scale of the        9443 1451
fission data of Wagemans et al. over the resonance at 0.0265 eV.  9443 1451
        In the energy range above 3 eV the small corrections      9443 1451
applied to the resonance parameters result in a decrease of the   9443 1451
average fission cross section and in an increase of the average   9443 1451
capture cross section,with a variation of the average total cross 9443 1451
section smaller than the errors of the experimental data of Harvey9443 1451
and Simpson.  The average values of the fission and capture cross 9443 1451
sections calculated with the new resonance parameters are shown in9443 1451
Table 5 and 6 along with the renormalized fission cross section of9443 1451
Weston and Todd and the values calculated from ENDF/B-VI.         9443 1451
                                                                  9443 1451
                  IV-CONCLUSION.                                  9443 1451
        The results of the recent measurement of the 241Pu fission9443 1451
cross section in the energy range from 0.002 eV to 4 eV of        9443 1451
Wagemans et al.  were used in a new evaluation of the resonance   9443 1451
parameters.  The accuracy of the calculated cross sections was    9443 1451
greatly improved in the resonance at 0.265 eV. The cross sections 9443 1451
averaged over this resonance should have the same accuracy as     9443 1451
the standard values at 0.0253 eV.  In the high energy region up   9443 1451
to 300 eV the SAMMY analysis of the new experimental data base    9443 1451
obtained by the renormalization of the experimental data is       9443 1451
recommended in order to improve the corrections to the resonance  9443 1451
parameters performed in the present work.                         9443 1451
